<p>Ask:</p>

<pre><code>"What are my top pages on mysite.com last 30 days?"
"Top 20 pages for example.com this week."
"Which URLs are getting the most traffic right now?"</code></pre>

<p>A typical response, formatted by Claude:</p>

<pre><code>Top pages for mysite.com (last 30 days):

  1. /                            14,232 views
  2. /pricing                      8,914 views
  3. /blog/llms-txt-explained      4,847 views
  4. /docs                         3,210 views
  5. /vs/google-analytics          2,891 views
  6. /blog/claude-mcp-setup        2,447 views
  7. /vs/plausible                 2,108 views
  8. /de/blog/mcp-server-anleitung 1,963 views
  9. /docs/setup                   1,442 views
 10. /privacy                      1,287 views</code></pre>

<p>Returns an array of <code>{ path, pageviews }</code> objects. Counts
include both direct browser visits and AI-mediated human browsing
(<code>ai_user_action</code>, e.g. Claude fetching a page on a user's
behalf). If you need to separate them, follow up with
<a href="/mcp/tools/traffic-class-breakdown"><code>traffic_class_breakdown</code></a>.</p>

<p>For long-tail SEO investigation you can stack this with
<a href="/mcp/tools/compare-periods"><code>compare_periods</code></a> to
identify pages that grew or fell sharply between periods.</p>
